      "lesson title": "Who Is Responsible for AI-Driven Construction Decisions?",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "As artificial intelligence becomes more widely used on construction projects, questions about accountability are becoming increasingly important for everyone involved. This lesson explores how responsibility is shared across the key parties in a construction project, including engineers, contractors, and developers, when AI tools are used to inform or drive decisions. You will learn how traditional roles and duties of care apply in an AI-assisted environment, and where gaps or uncertainties in accountability can arise. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of who is responsible when an AI-driven decision leads to an error, a delay, or a safety concern on site. No prior knowledge of AI or law is required, and the content is designed to be practical and relevant to everyday construction practice.",
